`palettejoin` Joins the palettes of 8-bit multiple PNG images, generating one 
single palette and adapting the images to the new palette.

The library libpng is required and can be downloaded in
<http://www.libpng.org/pub/png/libpng.html>.

The software can be compiled in the classic way:

  $ make
  # make install

Please use `palettejoin --help` to see the options provided.

`palettejoin` is free software and is licensed under the GPLv3 
<http://gnu.org/licenses/gpl.html>. See COPYING file for details.

The software home page is <http://palettejoin.googlecode.com/>.
